i feel the need to apologize...  I haven't been on Live Journal much....  seems I've been sucked into the world of myspace...  I never knew it would be so easy to find so many people from college....  So I've been networking and catching up over there...  and neglecting all of you...  I'm sorry....

Life at the moment is pretty good... compared to last week which was just way too hectic...  The beach party was this weekend and it was a major success, customers really enjoyed it. The Miss. Harrisburg competition was Sunday night.  It was a bit hard for me being a judge.  The two contestants were friends i hated to see either lose...  but congratulations to Buffy Buffington...  came out of retirement and won...not bad I say!  

Tonight is Goth Night....  Come on out and do the Dark Vogue...   he he, sorry inside joke.  Dancefloor opens at 10, monica's bartending as usual...  come on out and say hi :)

Ever have one of those weeks where no matter waht you do its just blah...... you feel blah, everything on tv is blah, everything on the computer is blah, you go out and blah.... so on and so forth... its been that kinda week for me. Even with Goth Night last night it was still just blah... I need pep, life, vibrance, something outta the ordinary...... any suggestions? 

The weekend is here and I'm pretty sure the bar will be full of drama once more, and to me that's blah. So even if I wanted a good weekend I'm sure at least one person will make a dramafest and it will be back to blah....  

so here's to hoping for excitement of some sort...

ok so my estimation...  Mysapce is good for networking and finding people I haven't seen in ages...  Live journal will deffinately be for my blogging...  way way to many people who don't need to know so much about me are on there...  that's ok though, its still cool.  But my heart belongs to LJ :)  he he

I broke down and joined the darkside....  my myspace I have been pulled into the myspace BALCKHOLE.  But if you're on there please friend me :)  Hey- I know, I know, but my little sister's on there so...  I don't want to hear it.

Ok... last night I went to see King Lear with Baby Gay.   We had dinner and then the play.  So the play was in my opinion mediocre. The actors were talking a bit too fast to catch all of the lines, one guy had an accent and it was very hard to understand any of his lines. The costumes were below par... of course I am a bit critical but I think 4 years and a degree in theatre allows me this. The lighting was good, actually I was impressed with the system they used...  The building however was WAY TOO HOT.  Some air flow woud have been nice. 

Being able to go out last night was nice, but not really enjoyable. The DJ sucked! I love to dance and I literally only felt compelled to dance to one song all night- the last one. Most of the people I like to hang out with weren't even out.   Never thought I'd say it, but I would have loved for Barry to have DJ-ed.  I went to an after party with Will. Bobbyboy183, Baby Gay, Jamie and Damion were there...  Phil and Monica joined us later...  it was fun.  deffinately made my night better.  Went to breakfast with Will...  I'm very glad he's grown up a bit.

I made stuffed peppers for the first time today, they turned out pretty good.  I also called my Gramm.  I always enjoy talking to her.  

Tonight- hopefully it will be busy :)

Last night went well... everyone seemed to enjoy themselves, we're trying to talk Barry into making it a monthly thing.

I'm off tonight... despite a bartender calling off... I'm not sure how things work anymore... seniority shcmenority.... i call Shenanagans!!!!!!!!!!!!!  any way its not important...

I'm going with Baby Gay to see King Lear in Lancaster..  should be interesting.  I've already seen this theatre troupe, The Aquilla Theatre Company, do King Lear when I was in college.  So I'm interested in seeing how it will vary from that experience :)  

I'll be out tonight for anyone who wants to come out and drink with me :)  I'll be at Stallions, possibly the barry for a bit... but come out and have fun with me!!

Tonight - DAYGLO colors optional!   

Come out and dance to your favorite 80's music- yes that's right, 80's music!!  

Come out and find out what Frankie really says...  come on, you know what I'm talking about...  admit it, we all love 80's music in some way... we all know the words and the tunes.  Hey, you could even request your favorite song and I'm pretty sure Barry will have it or its remix... he's an 80's junky too!   

Come on out and show us that you too love the 80's!!!  Monica will be behind the bar making you your favorite drinks...  Come out and help us show it was a good idea!  

Now, Relax get to it... (I could go all out cheesey here and put in tons of lyrics....  but I'll spare you.)

OK... so I managed to slice the top of my knuckle off today...  pointer finger on my left hand... the top one near my hand... 

How- well a photo frame in the bedroom fell down. The frame itself broke so I had the pictures and the glass sitting on the bed (stupid me), I forgot and put my hand down while reaching for something- slice... didn't really hurt, very clean, but pretty bad, several layers of skin are gone. I'm not one for doctors so I had Monica patch me up.

We'll see... its gonna leave one HELL of a scar though...

I have it wrapped as well as I can but its gonna be a challenge to bartend tonight. It hurts when I bend that finger and i use it for holding everything... Holding my jigger and opening bottles is going to prove interesting...  And what the hell am I gonna do if I get it wet?!  Its not like I can really fix anything at work....  And I sure as hell am not washing the damn thing- there's too much open and I'm not one for pain..  

yeah I can see it now- rum hurts like a bitch!  I'm going to try to wear a glove but that will look so stupid and I'm one of those people who would rather look nice than feel nice while in public.  Stupid, I know...  but I can't help it.  Plus all the gloves at the bar are really big and it wil effect everthing I try to do more than just with it wrapped...  what to do what to do.... 

Somehow I always manage to hurt myself at the most inopportuned times...  And this is going to take weeks to heal.. but its not like the Dr. could have done much...  I don't think stitches would have been given so they'd probably would of just wrapped up too...  UGHH

Edit-

I made it through the night with a completely dry hand, without the glove too... Woot Woot!! The tape and guaze made it hard to function though- I kept dropping things, and it kinda hurt when I had to bend it... It ended up taking me longer to count my money too... But at least its done and now I can just take it easy on that hand... :)

Tomorrow- shopping- I deserve a little spoiling...

So Monica wrote this in her journal... and instead of attempting to write something myself because it would probably depress me and I'd like to be in a good mood today... I'm copying hers... and only making a few changes...
 
Stoli O. Cosmopolitan, RIP  
Last year, at about 3:15 pm, on February 8th, our cat, Stoli O. Cosmopolitan died suddenly of freak natural causes, while coming home from a leash walk over at the museum. For those of you who knew Stoli O. or heard stories about him, you know how much he meant to Monica and I...We aren't typically 'those lesbians', but, he was a special creature, and truly was part of the family, and probably...ok, definitely would have been in family photos with us. He ate dinner with us, he waited up for Monica to get home from work, and wouldnt sleep until she came to bed. He was the sweetest creature ever, he would always sit on my lap in the living room but he would literally lounge in the living room until she came home from work, and then walk out to kitchen to greet her when she came in the door. He would wait in the bathroom doorway, yawning while she got ready for bed, and once she was in bed, he would clmib up after her, and sleep not in the middle, but, between her and the edge of the bed, as if he were protecting her...When I would get home from work he would follow me around the house.  Every time I was in the bathroom he would come in and beg to be loved.  He would lay on my lap for hours just purring and enjoying the fact that he was loved...  Stoli would, and did eat anything, literally. He was also very large..not fat, but just really, really big...( I almost think he may have had some sort of glandular issue that led to his death) He died when he was just under (possibly just over) a year old, and he was considerably larger than most full grown cats. His diet was insane. We asked the vet several times if it was dangerous to let him eat human food to the extent he did, and she said as long he liked it, and it wasnt making him sick, it was ok. He literally would want to eat anything he saw us eat. Even stuff cats aren't supposed to enjoy, like hot peppers, lettuce, and things cats aren't supposed to have a sense of taste or smell for, like pears, apples, and other sweet food. He was so interested in our food, and so smart (trainable), that, we taught him to wait patiently while we were eating, and never beg food, we eventually had him trained to know he was only allowed to eat off of plates or bowls if they were on the floor. There are so many other reasons I loved, and will miss Stoli O. Cosmopolitan..  We both will remember him for a very long time...
RIP Stoli O. Cosmopolitan, you are dearly missed, and shall remain in the hearts of those that knew and loved you.

Monica has also decided-

That in memory of our beloved cat, Stoli O. Cosmos will be served on special all night tonight at Stallions... no teasing her in any way or she will spank you.

Let me first say- I was very proud and impressed with Baby Gay last night.  It was his first night in training as a barback.  He picked things up faster than most and he had no problem figuring out the beer pull system.  I think he's gonna be good.  I'm glad to have him in that position...  can't say as much about the other new guys... not yet anyway.  We got out relatively early.  I had him show up at 8:30 so we wouldn't feel rushed.  I like to be able to explain things and give time for any questions to be answered.  Not that there where many questions.  David's been an employee long enough to see what goes on and he's helped out with the cleaning part a few times, that makes training a lot easier.  Things ran smootly...  which is always good and I know the bartenders both like him so its all gonna be good.  And since I'm not able to train him tonight I filled him in on a few things that should make his first Sat night run smoothly.    Overall it was good.

It ended up being a pretty decent night; but no til later in the night.  It was so nice out all day that we couldn't believe it took so long to get busy.  Today on the other hand...  well hopefully it will stop raining by this evening.  Cause we all know gay men hate to get their hair wet.   

Bobby, Joe, Adam and Kevin were out.   I even took time out to dance with them to "Since You've Been Gone."  How could I not- we all know that's the barback's tension breaker song....  I would have loved to have included David in the "secret", but he was on potty break...  It was really nice to see Joe, I've missed him.

Tonight...  hoping the rain will die down...  bartending as usual....  Hopefully someone is going to Eat n Park cause we have to pick up the "steeler" cookies we ordered last weekened...  

Tomorrow...  Costco with Barry.  Then about an hour of cooking for the Superbowl Party at the bar.  And by the way- The bar will open at 3pm....  food will be out around 6....  fun, prizes and lots of screaming at refs by your's truly....  Come out and see the Steelers kick Seattle's ass!!!!

Revelations- Tonight at 10PM 

Come out to hear industrial/ hard/ goth music.   Its not your average club music- but who wants to be average anyway?  And I made this cute little ad up- hope you like....

I had fun tonight... matt and I hung out for like 3 1/2 hours...  we talked, drank, talked, ate and talked some more...  it was good.  I love that guy, I've missed him.  I was also happy to introduce him to McGraths.....  of course everyone knows I love that place!!!!

well...  off to bed :)

so... today was the 31st...  I should have had all of my W2's by now.... yeah, that would have been nice.  I stopped by Neato to see if possibly by some mistake it was laying around...  nope and the new girl working said she hadn't recieved hers yet either...  but she called Tim, who I guess had asked Jon about it and he said they should be out soon....  WRONG ANSWER... they should have been out by today!!!!!  There's a law ya know... 

So what does this mean...  this means that tomorrow I am calling the better buisness bureau and telling them this story.

Also...  it was the first time I've been in there since I was let go.  I bought myself some yummy black bean hummus and jalapeno and feta salsa....  its gonna be an explosion of my taste buds when I get my nachos tomorrow :)

Other tax news... the bar screwed up again this year...  we told Barry about it at the beginning of the year cause they barely took any federal tax out of my checks last year... this year they only took $2.....  yeah, so I'm getting a whole hell of alot less back... GRRRRRR   But we picked up a new W4? sheet today, I'm going to fill it out and make sure the bar has the right info instead of relying on someone else to make sure... even if it is their job... I'm not going to get screwed again.

Got loads of pictures developed today....  yay :)  Made copies of some for my little sister- who by the way is going to come visit sometime in the near future...

Tonight...  I'm going to hang out with ...  its gonna be a nice time to talk.  I've missed him, he hasn't been out since the whole thing with SM....  and it will be good to talk and listen :)
